cope data access with ctx.user!.userId for protected endpoints to prevent cross-user data leaks.","ai.generate requires prompt/messages/media input, and supports optional images/audios, optional schema (structured output), and optional tools.","ai.imageGen generates an image with Gemini image model and returns { image: { data, mimeType, bytes } }. It enforces strict per-app limits and output-byte caps (maxOutputBytes hard-capped at 1,000,000).","Thinking mode is configured with thinkingMode: 'NONE' | 'FAST' | 'DEEP' (default: 'FAST').","Frontend image preprocessing helper: use { image } from @appdeploy/client and call image.resizeIfNeeded(file) before sending to backend ai.* endpoints.","When sending camera photos, resize/compress client-side before ai.* calls for faster responses and to reduce payload-limit failures.","Deterministic preprocess target: max dimension <= 1600px and total pixels <= 2MP before converting to base64.","For OCR/transcription from images, prefer ai.ocr({ images, prompt? }) instead of ad-hoc ai.generate prompts.","For schema-based extraction from text or images, use ai.extract({ schema, prompt, content?, images? }). Pass scraped text via `content`, not by embedding it in `prompt`.","ai.extract applies safer defaults and retries when model output is empty or malformed JSON.","For fixed-label classification tasks, prefer ai.classify({ labels, images, prompt }) over manual prompt parsing.","ai.classify applies safer defaults and retries for empty/unparseable model outputs.","ai.scrape accepts an http/https URL and returns { text, title?, status } for AI-friendly page extraction.","ai.run executes a bounded generate->tool loop (default 5 steps, hard cap 10).","For structured ai.run output, declare a reserved tool named emit_result with a strict JSON schema; when the model calls it, ai.run ends and returns result.data.","Use isAppDeployRpcError(error) in catch blocks when you need statusCode/responseBody from SDK RPC failures.","When using ai.run